<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
  <title>Missing SIQ Counter Statistics File</title>
</head>
<body role="main">
  <h1>Missing SIQ Counter Statistics File</h1>
  
  <p>The expected SIQ Counter Statistics file was not found in the AWS S3 bucket.</p>
  
  <table style="margin: 20px 0; border-collapse: collapse;">
    <tr>
      <td style="padding: 8px; font-weight: bold;">Check Date:</td>
      <td style="padding: 8px;"><%= @check_date %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding: 8px; font-weight: bold;">Expected File:</td>
      <td style="padding: 8px;"><code><%= @expected_filename %></code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding: 8px; font-weight: bold;">Period:</td>
      <td style="padding: 8px;"><%= @month_name %> <%= @year %></td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  
  <p>The MonthlyCounterStatsJob will continue checking daily until the file is available.</p>
  
  <h2>Please verify:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>The file has been uploaded to the SIQ S3 bucket</li>
    <li>The filename matches the expected format: <code>fulcrum_metric_totals-YYYY-MM.csv</code></li>
    <li>AWS credentials in <code>config/scholarlyiq.yml</code> are correct</li>
    <li>Bucket name and region are configured properly</li>
  </ol>
  
  <p>The job will automatically process the file once it becomes available.</p>
</body>
</html>
